# Server (`apps/server`)

## Entry & order (`src/index.ts`)

CORS → Better Auth `/api/auth/*` → **billing webhook** (`express.raw`) → `express.json` → `/api` rate limit → `requireApiAccess` → routers → `errorHandler`.

## Routers

- **`/api/verify`** — `GET /:nafdac`, `POST /batch` (+ `verifyPlanRateLimiter`).
- **`/api/products`** — search (Pro).
- **`/api/bot`** — `requireBotInternalToken` on each route: `POST /activity`, `POST /status`, `POST /billing/initialize-bot-pro`.
- **`/api/keys`** — session auth per handler: keys CRUD, `GET /metrics`, billing `status|account|transactions`, `POST billing/initialize-pro`, `POST billing/cancel-subscription`.
- **`/api/public`** — `GET /verify/:nafdac` + internal secret (Next BFF).

## Core services (pointers)

| Area | Files |
|------|--------|
| Verify + bot quota | `verifyNafdacController.ts`, `verifyBatchController.ts`, `botPlanService.ts` (`resolveBotPlan`, `getBotStatusSnapshot`, `assertBotDailyQuotaAllows`, `incrementBotDailyVerify`) |
| NAFDAC scrape + cache | `verifyService.ts`, `nafdacRegistrationClient.ts`, `nafdacHtmlParser.ts` |
| API plan / monthly quota | `apiPlanService.ts`, `monthlyApiQuotaService.ts` |
| Paystack | `paystackService.ts`, `paystackWebhookService.ts`, `billing*Controller.ts`, `botBillingInitializeController.ts` |
| Product search | `productSearchController.ts`, `productSearchService.ts` |
| Keys | `apiKeyController.ts`, `apiKeyService.ts` |

## Bot billing initialize

`botBillingInitializeController.ts`: `WEB_APP_URL` → origin; `callback_url` → `/bot/billing/success?via=telegram`; synthetic email `bot-tg-{telegramId}@{PAYSTACK_BOT_CHECKOUT_EMAIL_DOMAIN || 9jacheckr.xyz}`.

## Conventions

- ESM + **`.js` imports** in TS source.
- JSON errors: `ok`, `code`, `message` per `types/types.ts`.
- Use **`logger`** for ops logs.

See **`9jacheckr-overview.mdc`** for full handbook.
